{"type":"text","timestamp":1781762877308,"sessionID":"ses_126aa1e86ffe3voro0xMEMegIU","part":{"id":"prt_ed957ca39001tP7b2AxWTgkHvs","messageID":"msg_ed957bb72001yEPgUg0JVqBslj","sessionID":"ses_126aa1e86ffe3voro0xMEMegIU","type":"text","text":"One high-risk area is the async scan runnerвҖҷs interaction with cancellation and post-processing. I need the tail of `memory-index.ts` and the ingest queue implementation to verify whether partial writes are reported safely.","time":{"start":1781762869817,"end":1781762877304},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_00bb168e403b2046016a338b35c9c081919cc4f745778e98cd","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781762877362,"sessionID":"ses_126aa1e86ffe3voro0xMEMegIU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hoemv7dh9GuNrbVKxfR5D0kA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts","offset":1316,"limit":1400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1316:           // Per-folder synchronous DB work; yield + cancel-check between folders so a\n1317:           // large affected set cannot block the event loop (same rationale as the\n1318:           // metadata-edge sweep above).\n1319:           if (++chainYieldCount % 50 === 0) {\n1320:             if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n1321:               return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n1322:             }\n1323:             await new Promise<void>((resolve) => setImmediate(resolve));\n1324:           }\n1325:           const rows = selectDocIds.all(folder) as Array<{ document_type: string; id: number }>;\n1326:           const docIds: Record<string, number> = {};\n1327: \n1328:           for (const row of rows) {\n1329:             if (row.document_type && typeof row.id === 'number') {\n1330:               docIds[row.document_type] = row.id;\n1331:             }\n1332:           }\n1333: \n1334:           if (Object.keys(docIds).length >= 2) {\n1335:             const chainResult = createSpecDocumentChain(docIds);\n1336:             chainsCreated += chainResult.inserted;\n1337:             foldersProcessed++;\n1338:           }\n1339:         }\n1340: \n1341:         if (chainsCreated > 0) {\n1342:           console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Created ${chainsCreated} causal chain edges across ${foldersProcessed} spec folders`);\n1343:         }\n1344:       }\n1345:     } catch (err: unknown) {\n1346:   